<header id="masthead">

    <div class="row header-row">
        <div id="logo-tagline" class="col-md-3">
            <a href="/">
                <img src="/styles/youjuke_logo_0.png" id="logo-img">
                <p id="slogan">Sick of algorithms telling you what to listen to?</p>
            </a>
        </div>

        <div id="current-track-wrapper" class="col-md-6">
            <div id="play-track-container">
                <button type="button" class="btn" id="start-listening"><i
                        class="large material-icons play-pause">play_circle_outline</i></button>
                <div id="current-track-box"></div>

            </div>

        </div>

        <div id="header-menu-buttons" class="col-md-3">

            <div id="volume-sign-in">
                <input id="volume" type="range" min="0" max="100" step="1" value="90"></input>
                <a href="/logout"><button type="button" class="btn btn-secondary" id="sign-out-button" data-toggle="modal"
                    data-target="#sign-in" data-whatever="@mdo">Sign Out</button></a>
            </div>

            <div id="user-info">
                <div id="welcome-box">Welcome</div>
            </div>

        </div>





</header>



<div class="container main-container">

    <div class="row main-row">

        <div class="col-lg-5 col-md-5" id="left-panel">

            <ul class="nav nav-tabs" id="myTabLeft" role="tablist">
                <li class="nav-item">
                    <a class="nav-link active" id="queue-tab" data-toggle="tab" href="#queue" role="tab"
                        aria-controls="queue" aria-selected="true"><i class="material-icons">playlist_play</i></a>
                </li>

                <li class="nav-item">
                    <a class="nav-link" id="chat-tab" data-toggle="tab" href="#chat" role="tab" aria-controls="chat"
                        aria-selected="false"><i class="material-icons">forum</i></a>
                </li>
            </ul>

            <div class="tab-content" id="myTabContentLeft">
                <div class="tab-pane fade show active" id="queue" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="queue-tab">
                    <div class="wrapper queued-track-wrapper">

                        <div id="left-panel-title">
                        </div>
                        <div class="queued-track-container"></div>
                    </div>

                </div>
                <div class="tab-pane fade" id="chat" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="chat-tab">
                    <div class="chat-container"></div>
                    <p>Chat feature coming to future version of Youjuke</p>

                </div>

            </div>



        </div>

        <div class="col-lg-7 col-md-7" id="right-panel">

            <ul class="nav nav-tabs" id="myTabRight" role="tablist">
                <li class="nav-item">
                    <a class="nav-link active" id="search-tab" data-toggle="tab" href="#search" role="tab"
                        aria-controls="search" aria-selected="true"><i class="material-icons">search</i></a>
                </li>

                <li class="nav-item">
                    <a class="nav-link" id="room-info-tab" data-toggle="tab" href="#room-info" role="tab"
                        aria-controls="room-info" aria-selected="false"><i class="material-icons">place</i></a>
                </li>
                <li class="nav-item">
                    <a class="nav-link" id="graph-tab" data-toggle="tab" href="#graph" role="tab" aria-controls="graph"
                        aria-selected="false"><i class="material-icons">bubble_chart</i></a>
                </li>
                <li class="nav-item">
                    <a class="nav-link" id="fav-tab" data-toggle="tab" href="#fav" role="tab" aria-controls="fav"
                        aria-selected="false"><i class="material-icons">grade</i></a>
                </li>
                <li class="nav-item">
                    <a class="nav-link" id="rankings-tab" data-toggle="tab" href="#rankings" role="tab"
                        aria-controls="rankings" aria-selected="false"><i class="material-icons">show_chart</i></a>

                </li>
                <li class="nav-item">
                    <a class="nav-link" id="info-tab" data-toggle="tab" href="#info" role="tab" aria-controls="info"
                        aria-selected="false"><i class="material-icons">help</i></a>
                </li>
            </ul>

            <div class="tab-content" id="myTabContentRight">

                <div class="tab-pane fade show active" id="search" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="search-tab">

                    <div class="input-group mb-3">
                        <input type="text" class="form-control" id="search-input"
                            placeholder="enter track title or artist..." aria-label="Deezer search"
                            aria-describedby="basic-addon2">
                        <div id="clear-search">&times;</div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="results-and-lyrics">
                        <div class="search-results-container">
                        </div>

                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="tab-pane fade" id="room-info" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="room-info-tab">
                    <div class="room-description-container">
                        <h3>{{room}}</h3>
                        <p>{{description}}</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="tab-pane fade chart-container" id="graph" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="graph-tab">
                    <div class="canvas-container"><canvas id="myChart" width="200" height="200"></canvas></div>
                </div>

                <div class="tab-pane fade chart-container" id="fav" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="fav-tab">
                    <div class="favs-container">
                        <div id="favs-list"></div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="tab-pane fade chart-container" id="rankings" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="rankings-tab">
                    <div class="rankings-container">
                        <div id="rankings-list"></div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="tab-pane fade" id="info" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="info-tab">
                    <div class="about-app">

                        <h3>What is Youjuke?</h3>

                        <p>Youjuke is a music forum that allows groups of visitors to compile
                            a shared playlist and listen to it together, live. Anyone can add a track
                            to the playlist, but it is up to all users as a whole to decide the order of the
                            playlist. Whether you want to share tracks with a larger audience,
                            or want to break out into a virtual party with friends, Youjuke has you covered.</p>

                        <p>Want to know which music the audience likes? Youjuke keeps track of favorite tracks.
                        </p>

                        <p>Let you be the algorithm to your listening party.</p>

                        <h3>How do I use Youjuke?</h3>

                        <ul>
                            <li>First, create an account or log in.</li>
                            <li>Click on the 'rooms' tab to see existing rooms. Click on one you would like to enter.
                            </li>
                            <li>If you want to create a room, click on the '+' tab.</li>
                            <li>Once you are in your room, there may be songs already cued up. Click on the play button
                                to begin.</li>
                            <li>Due to licensing, this version of Youjuke currently only plays previews and not complete
                                songs. Full lyrics may also not be available for songs.
                            </li>
                            <li>Like with radio, as you (or others in the room) listen to songs, they will be cycled out
                                of the cue and
                                the playlist will be updated live.</li>
                            <li>Want to hear that song you just added more than any of
                                the others already in the playlist? Give that song a thumbs up to vote up its position.
                                If that song has more
                                has more thumbs-ups than the other tracks, it will come on after the current song. </li>
                            <li>Hate a song in the playlist? Give that song a thumbs down. The most down-voted songs
                                will appear
                                at the bottom of the playlist after the current song ends.</li>
                            <li>There are graph tabs that show charts of music preferences of users and lists of
                                favorite tracks of both you and other users.</li>
                        </ul>


                        <h3>More information</h3>

                        <p>YouJuke was developed by Greg Allebach and Patrick Urbankowski.</p>


                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

        </div>


    </div>

</div>

